extends ./layouts/layout

block page-title
  title Wiki Thanks
  link(rel="icon",
    href="favicon.ico",
    type="image/x-icon")

block head
  include ./includes/header.jade

block content
  #main.container.row
    .container.row
      .col-md-12.lead 
        h2 Increasing the civility in the world
    .container.row
      .col-md-12 Wikipedia is the encyclopedia that anybody can edit. And "thanks" is a free compliment that anybody can give. But both can sometimes be hard to do.
    .container.row
      .col-md-12 This site should make editing Wikipedia easier for the would-be editor be showing examples of how simple and non-intimidating some of the edits are. And it should make saying thank-you easier for the would-be Decent Fellow Human by giving a one-click option for sending a automated thank-you to the editor through Wikipedia's API.
      
